## Troubleshooting

### Emulator Won't Open
```powershell
# Check emulator is listed
emulator -list-avds

# Start manually
emulator -avd pixel_5_-_api_34

# Then run
npm run android
```

### Port Already in Use
```powershell
# Kill process on port 8081
npx react-native start --reset-cache
# or
Get-Process -Id (Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 8081).OwningProcess | Stop-Process -Force
```

### Clear Everything
```powershell
# Nuclear option
Remove-Item -Recurse -Force node_modules
Remove-Item package-lock.json
npm install
npx expo start --clear
```

---

## When to Use Bare React Native

You **don't need** bare React Native for this project. Expo handles:
- ✅ Firebase/Firestore
- ✅ Offline SQLite
- ✅ Secure storage
- ✅ File system (receipts)
- ✅ Navigation

Use bare RN only if you need:
- ❌ Custom native modules not in Expo
- ❌ Brownfield (existing native app)
- ❌ Very specific native tweaks

